The paper discusses training deep neural networks using weakly-labeled data, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of semi-supervised learning. The specific application domain is document ranking, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP), suggesting that cs.IR and cs.CL are likely sub-categories. The use of deep neural networks and the focus on learning representations suggests that cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the potential use of image data for document ranking (e.g., for visual search) suggests that cs.CV may also be a relevant sub-category.
